{"article_id":"i4X13t1XjdJRDcPl","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" For them to go after the U.N. ambassador ,","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"who had nothing to do with Benghazi","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"and was simply making a presentation","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"based on the intelligence","depth":12},{"id":4,"text":"that she had received ,","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"and to besmirch her reputation ,","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"is outrageous , \"","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Mr. Obama said ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"his eyes flashing with anger .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Describing Ms. Rice ' s conduct as \" exemplary , \"","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"he warned","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that her critics have \" got a problem with me. \"","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Almost daring them to a confirmation battle ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"he vowed to nominate Ms. Rice","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"if he determined","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"that she was the right person for secretary of state .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s remarks drew an equally angry response from Senators McCain and Lindsey Graham .","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"In a statement","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"issued after the news conference ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Mr. Graham reiterated","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"that he would oppose \" anyone","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"who is up to their eyeballs in the Benghazi debacle . \"","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"By contrast , the president struck an almost elegiac tone","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"in discussing the sex scandal","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"that forced the resignation of David H. Petraeus as director of the Central Intelligence Agency .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Mr. Petraeus ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"he said ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"told him","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"that he did not meet his own standards","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"for holding the job .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Mr. Obama added ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"\" We are safer","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"because of the work","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Dave Petraeus has done , \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"voicing hope","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"that the scandal would end up as a \" single side note on what has otherwise been an extraordinary career . \"","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Mr. Obama was cautious","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"in responding to questions","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"about whether he should have been told earlier about the investigation into the relationship between Mr. Petraeus and his biographer , Paula Broadwell ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"with the president saying","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"that he would leave it to the F.B.I . to explain its \" protocols. \"","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"while he offered no criticism of the investigation ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"he appeared to leave himself room","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"to do so in the future ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"should new information emerge .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"\" I am withholding judgment","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"with respect to how the entire process","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"surrounding General Petraeus","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"came up , \"","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"In laying out his position on the budget ,","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"Mr. Obama emphasized","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"that debate over taxes had been central to the election","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"he just won","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"and reprised many of the themes","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"he had struck on the campaign trail .","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"The president urged Republicans to go along with his proposal","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"to extend the Bush-era tax cuts on all personal income up to $ 250,000 a year ,","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"noting","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"that people","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"who made more than that amount","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"would also benefit from such an extension .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"Please verify","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":3},{"id":82,"text":"\" But when it comes to the top 2 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"what I ' m not going to do is extend further a tax cut for folks","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"who don ' t need it ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"which would cost close to a trillion dollars , \"","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"Mr. Obama said .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"While he insisted","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that the tax cuts for income above $ 250,000 must expire ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Mr. Obama did not stipulate","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"that the top rate would revert to 39.6 percent ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"as it was in the Clinton administration .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Mr. Bush signed a bill a decade ago","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"reducing it to 35 percent ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"where it has remained .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s stance appeared to leave room for the White House and Republicans to negotiate a tax rate somewhere in between","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"and then raise additional revenue","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"by restricting tax deductions and credits on high incomes .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"\" I don ' t expect Republicans simply to adopt my budget , \"","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"\" That ' s not realistic .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"So I recognize","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that we ' re going to have to compromise . \"","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"Still , Mr. Obama said","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"he could envision a situation","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"in which there was no agreement","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"and all the tax cuts expired .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Such an outcome would be a \" rude shock \" for middle-class people ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"he said ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"and could set off a recession .","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"\" It would be a bad thing , \"","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"he said .","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"\" It is not necessary . \"","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"By suggesting","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"he was willing to accept failed negotiations ,","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"Mr. Obama was in part trying to give himself more leverage than in 2010 ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"when fears about the economy and its impact on his political standing caused him to reverse course and accept an extension of all the Bush tax cuts in exchange for additional stimulus .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"This time , however , the economy is somewhat stronger ,","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Mr. Obama has no more elections in front of him","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"- as he pointed out on Wednesday -","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"and the package of budget changes","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"set to take effect on Jan. 1","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"includes both tax increases and military cuts","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"that Republicans generally oppose .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Speaker John A. Boehner , the effective leader of the Republican Party , said","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"Republicans were not ready to accept Mr. Obama ' s proposal","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"because it would \" hurt our economy","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"and make job creation more difficult. \"","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"But he added","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"that there was a \" spirit of cooperation \"","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"that had infused Washington","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"and that gave him optimism","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"that some sort of deal would eventually come to pass .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"Republicans say","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"they will find a way","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"to raise enough money","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"to reduce the deficit","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"without lifting the top rates .","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"Back-of-the-envelope math suggests","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"that eliminating all tax breaks for the top 2 percent of households would raise about $ 2 trillion over 10 years , more than the $ 1.6 trillion","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"that the White House demands , as part of a $ 3 trillion deficit-reduction package over 10 years .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"But having all of the additional tax revenue come from the restriction of tax breaks would require getting rid of virtually every such provision , like the home-mortgage deduction , in the tax code on top incomes .","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"Allowing tax rates to rise on the wealthy","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"- to the Clinton-era levels , or a few percentage points below them -","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"puts much more money on the table","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"and would allow more moderate changes to deductions ,","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"Democrats argue .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"Looking beyond the immediate fiscal challenges ,","depth":6},{"id":148,"text":"Mr. Obama expressed optimism about one major goal","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"- immigration legislation -","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"and caution about another , climate change .","depth":7},{"id":151,"text":"The president said","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"he intended to pursue comprehensive immigration legislation ,","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"and noted","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"that the election had prompted reflection among Republicans about their opposition to such an effort .","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"Even as he criticized Mr. McCain on Benghazi ,","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"he cited his support for an overhaul of immigration law as an indication","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"that it could pass .","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"On climate change , Mr. Obama played down expectations for any major initiative .","depth":5},{"id":159,"text":"He spoke of holding a conversation with scientists and engineers about fresh ideas ,","depth":6},{"id":160,"text":"but said","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"more ambitious legislation would come","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"only after the economy strengthened .","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"\" We ' re still trying to debate","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"whether we can just make sure that middle-class families don ' t get a tax hike , \"","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"\" That should be easy .","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"This one ' s hard . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":335,"left":231,"right":334,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":231,"left":219,"right":230,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":219,"left":189,"right":218,"relation":"joint","nuclear